==English==
===Verb===
'''to bisect'''

# To [[cut]] or [[divide]] into two parts.
# {{geometry}} To divide an [[angle]] or [[line segment]] into two [[equal]] parts.



===Noun===
#([[stamp-collecting]]) An envelope or a card (or a [[fragment]]) showing an affixed cut half of a regular issued [[stamp]], over which one or more [[postal]] markings have been applied. Typically used in [[wartime]] when normal lower rate stamps may not be available.
# {{geometry}} A [[bisector]], dividing into two equal parts.

